text: It's about 90% my son's build, but I tweaked it a bit because some of his mana base and a couple of spells are suboptimal.
how old is he?
oh dang
much older than i expected
I'm old
also explains why the deck is as decent as it is
Yeah I've had him playing since he was 13. He buys his own singles and everything. I never let him get packs unless it was through winning them. His collection is pretty good.

The deck was totally his idea as well. When samut got printed he was stoked and started brewing with her. This build is what he came to around 3 weeks ago with RIX'S release. At first the deck was a cute humans tribal deck. Now it's a damn nuisance.
It’s a pretty nice Nya good-stuff pow-pow deck.
a couple of thoughts: hanweird militia captain doesn’t seem to do anything for the deck, and that new pay 5 to draw a card land seems like it would be great in this deck
there is a semi-token build to it, but he seems the weakest of the bunch

I’d put Scooze in there, if possible.
I might also run [[dusk // dawn]]

text: Yeah militia cap is a hold over. Scooze is a great replacement. Dusk would work as well so I'll probably find a slot. Vent maw is fantastic, good find henry. Extra combat is a direction I suggested to him because he started to notice late game he would have a lot of mana and little to do with it. Hence the aggrevated assault + bear umbra/nature's will combo.
Also the Aurelia and combat celebrant.
I’d consider Asceticism or Privileged  Position too as protection.
Asceticism is in there. Position is another awesome suggestion. Thanks.
I missed it. Sorry.

No worries at all. The deck has been running so strong lately I told him I'm going to showcase it because it raises so many eyebrows in our local meta. I don't think most people, myself included, realized how much of a threat a well built samut deck can pose.
Anytime a Commander has doublestrike and haste there’s reason to worry.

Land Tax: It' s a great card, but here I don't see anything that would abuse shuffle effects (Top, Rack) and you don't have ways to put those extra lands into play. It winds up being a way to hit your land drops IF you're behind someone. That's not bad or anything, and Land Tax is never bad, but I think I'd rather just run a draw spell or a ramp spell if I'm not really taking advantage of what Tax offers.
Or Abundance to combo w Sylvan Library
it’s a form of card advantage, but it isn’t a be all end all, that’s for sure
if there’s a way to turn those lands into something else with things like faithless looting or something, that’s good synergy
Yeah. I’m into trying the Abundance/SL combo.
There isn't though in this deck that I see
<@U6LUSCS1J> Is MLD  a common thing in your meta?
there’s also not a ton of basic in the deck
Yep

If MLD isn't a thing, I'd be tempted to replace the two Talismans with Nature's Lore and Farseek. Both fetch duals at the same CMC and lands are harder to remove than artifacts, and they don't hit you for a damage when tapped.
But if you see mass land removal then it's good to diversify
Another angle there - I was hit with Nature’s Revolt/Linvala lock this weekend where I can’t tap my lands for mana and used exclusively land ramp.

Yeah. I don't see MLD and I still try to diversify, but I've also had plenty of games where I've cursed myself for not being greedy with land ramp after a vandalblast takes out four rocks or something
The guy was running a complete hate deck and later got out Stony Silence so he had everyone locked out of resources.
